Reviews: Purchased this refurbished iPhone 5s to save a bit; opted to not buy a brand new iPhone 5s and also skip the iPhone 6 series as it seemed a little pricey for me. This buy satisfied my needs, it came in decent packaging, and as described showed little wear. A few small marks and dents in the metal outer casing exist, but the phone is scratch-free. The battery life seems fine, and the phone operates to full capacity with all the apps I've downloaded. The vibrate function is a little rattly, it doesn't sound perfect but this isn't a new phone. The hardest part about buying this refurbished phone, was the activation part with my carrier. Took several hours and changing of a few identification numbers with the phone, because those IDs had been previously used by another person. I am fairly confident I would buy again in this manner instead of buying new, as long as the quality of the product is the same as this one.

Reviews: I was very happy to find this iPhone 5S for such a good price, since it had been certified refurbished.  I bought it a few months ago and it worked wonderfully.  However I started noticing issues with the sound after about two months.  I could only use the speaker function to dial and to receive calls.  If I used earbuds, it seemed to work better.  However, yesterday when I put my earbuds in to listen to music, no sound came out at all.  When I tried to answer a phone cal, I put it on speaker and could barely understand anything my friend was saying.  She couldn't understand me either.I'm pretty disappointed with the quality of this phone and wish that these issues had occurred within a month so I could return this phone and get my money back.  Unfortunately it's too late now and I'm stuck with a phone that can't call or receive calls and can't even act as an iPod for music.  Pretty disappointing indeed.

Reviews: I have nothing but good things to say about the seller but the phone was disappointing. We didn't keep this phone bc it turned out to have been made for the Japanese market so we couldn't turn off the camera shutter sound. Additionally, the battery would sporadically die. However, when we contacted the seller about swapping it out for a phone that would be made for the US, he was amazingly responsive & 100% honest that they could not guarantee we would not get another phone with the same feature. I was impressed by how quickly the seller returned my emails and that they were honest about what they could provide. We had previously purchased a refurb phone for my daughter and have had no issues, but this is the 2nd refurb 5S we've gotten recently (the first was a Groupon deal that was also returned) and it's the 2nd one that ended up being made for the Japanese market and could not have the shutter sound muted. I ended up buying directly from a seller on Swappa so that I could be sure I would not have this same issue for a 3rd time. I would say that at this point, it's going to be hit or miss buying a 5S so as long as you know you can return it if there are any problems, it's worth the savings to give it a try.

I can't say for sure why this happens but I'm pretty tech savvy and I've tried everything under the sun to make it stop to no avail. So when taking a picture in a quiet environment I would get "the look" from people after shattering the quiet with my phone. I have to fly home to see my family this week but I might have to travel without a phone b/c I have tech service  scheduled with the Apple Store for Monday or I might end up having to get a new phone. Reviews: This phone came packaged securely and the phone was in excellent condition, it looked brand new even. I turned it on and it even had some battery charge. Know you will need a SIM physically in it to set it up (any SIM will do, it can be a non-working SIM, I used an old one I had) thanks to Apple. Once you do you can have it set up with your Apple ID or a new one and start as a new phone or restore. I loved that I could set this phone prior to activating the phone on my UK SIM (because I had a random SIM hanging around), downloading the apps I needed and getting everything going. So far everything looks good.The minus star goes to the seller using a mailing label on the back of the phone telling the customer to call them for any problems. I get that but it took me no joke 20 minutes to get the sticker off and I scratched my phone a bit with my nails. Plus messed up my nail polish but I can get over that. If I was using an opaque case the sticker would be fine but I ordered a partially seethru case for my GOLD phone. The scratches aren't that noticeable but I think the seller should change the sticker to something that comes off easier.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: Perfect!  After reading several of the 1 or 2 star reviews, I was very hesitant to purchase this phone.  But I figured that it had a 90 day warranty, so if it showed up defective/scratched/broken/etc., I would just return it.  Phone arrived on time.  After initial inspection, there were no cracks/scratches/etc.  It looked like new.  I was then a bit worried about the functionality.  I've had it all weekend plus a few days, and have gone through most functions that I can thin of, and the only problem I encountered was that the speaker didn't work during one outgoing call (which happened a few times with other phones I've owned).  A restart of the phone and it worked fine (probably an issue with the multiple BT devices that I have connected to the phone).  The last thing I was worried about was the battery life.  If this phone had been used (and then refurbished), the battery life would not be what it was when new.  That was not an issue at all.  The battery life is phenomenal.  The phone was either never used for any length of time (e.g. opened, and then returned to the store for whatever reason, and then sent to a 3rd party refurbisher and then purchased by me), or, it was used very lightly, and then refurbished (which included putting a new battery in it).  Either way, I'm very happy.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I was initially wary of this purchase as the reviews weren't the greatest - 40% negative and 60% positive. That said, I eventually realised the *product* reviews relate to a variety of Sellers, as when you select a certain combo of colour/size, the Seller changes. With that in mind, I was careful to review the Seller specifically (on their main site) - since BuySpry had very positive reviews I moved forward.The phone is in great condition physically - no scratches or wear and tear are visible. It arrived nicely packaged in a plastic case, with protective plastic on the screen/back as well. It also arrives with a card from the seller advising to call a certain number if there was any issues, as well as a "Certified Refurbished by Amazon" card which was comforting as Amazon backed the product. There was no issue setting up - my SIM fit and it was unlocked and works with Vodafone.I've only had it for less than a week, however, so far it works fine with very minimal issues. The battery is not the best (when at 10% it suddenly dies), however, it was to be expected with refurb. It lasts the majority of the day if you're not using a lot of apps (esp. FaceTime) which is similar to any iPhone after months of use.I live in Australia ordered the phone on a Monday evening (AEST) and it arrived by Thursday @ 4pm (AEST), although guarantee delivery wasn't till Friday. This was fantastic given it was coming from the states and I was in a pinch as my previous phone had been stolen.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: MAJOR PRO:Ordered the iPhone 6 Plus 64GB. Received it in a Amazon "Certified Refurbished" white box with the phone, a generic charger, and generic lightning cable. No earphones as stated by their description of purchase. All was great! No scratches, dings, or anything so it felt brand new. Set up was easy. Screen was great, sound was great, and battery life is superb. I came from using a Samsung Galaxy S4 with a replaceable battery, but even replacing them the batteries never last me a full 12 hours. I put this iPhone to the test by downloading and using the same apps I use for my Samsung. Mindblown. Unplugged the iPhone at 6:30AM with 100% charge, came back home at 10:00PM with 45% left, used it for a some more and slept at 12AM with 33% charge left. Wow. My samsung would've died at 9AM, recharge, and then die again at 3PM, and then recharge again at 7PM.MAJOR CON:Anyway, the main reason why I gave this only  a 4 star is because the version of iPhone I received is a Japanese iPhone. I CANNOT turn the  camera sound shutter off. Only phones in Japan have this. How do I know? I've lived there and all my friends' phones (including iphones) cannot have the camera shutter sound off even if silent due to Japanese regulation/law that passed back in the early 2000s. Apple and all cell phone companies must comply. I've been an iPhone user back in the day (3G/3GS/4S) and know how to silent this by (duh) putting the phone to silent mode. Nada. Googled a solution only to find out that I have to jailbreak it and remove/change a system UI file. Unfortunately, I don't want to do that and can't do that since I have the latest iOS version 10.3.2 (as of May 2017) so I'm stuck with an annoying camera shutter sound being always on.CONCLUSION:Other than the Major con, happy with the purchase!

Reviews: I wanted to save some money now I'm wishing I just paid full price. This is the most I've ever spent for a phone and I've never had so many problems. I've had 3 issues with my refurbished iPhone 6plus and now I have to buy a new phone. I'm past the 90 day warranty, and Apple won't help because it is refurbished.I've done some research on iFixit, Reddit, YouTube, Yahoo  answers, etc.. I see these are all common problems with 3RD PARTY REFURBISHED iPhones. Seems like these guys cant put a phone together like they do back in FoxCon.After this HORRIBLE phone experience, I will never ever buy a refurbished product on Amazon again.1. When I bought the 128 6plus iPhone there was a problem with the charger cable connection. It took a few tries to get the phone to start charging. I said ok, I can live with that. Well it turns out I can't. It's extremely annoying and getting worse every day. Now o sit there for a few minutes trying to make a connection. I try my wife and kids cables to no avail. Theirs work perfectly , mine won't. Hard to use a phone you can't charge! Plus I can't keep the damned thing connected to my MacBook when I am syncing, updating, or transferring files. Had to get a new cable right away because the cheap flimsy cord they send you is useless.2: BIGGEST PROBLEM: " ghost touches"  or "phantom touches" I started experiencing phantom touches all over my screen, apps opening and closing, random calls made, emails, texts, music playing, etc. only way to stop is to quickly lock phone. Restarting doesn't help since this is a hardware issue. Rendering phone COMPLETELY USELESS for hours on end! Comes and goes randomly at most inconvenient times.3: Then the complete opposite happens. I try to touch the screen and I don't get any response at all. Tap tap tap away- nada. This leaves me with the option to use Siri only, since the physical buttons are the only way to control the phone. Again, restarting does not help.Thanks for nothing Amazon, feels like I got ripped off on eBay or Craigslist!

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I've had this phone almost a week and have had absolutely nothing to complain about. Granted it's only been several days nonetheless the phone so far is great. I bought the 128gb space gray 6 plus Certified Refurbished. There were less gb choices that cost more which made me question the quality of the product.Will it overheat? Will the battery drain quickly? No and no. I've purposefully left my charger off to the side and used Netflix and Pandora (apps I figured would test the battery) and surprisingly there was, I think, a 38% charge the next day. The battery was my biggest concern and it is safe to say I am no longer concerned.How is the exterior? Even though I had already planned on buying a case that would cover the phone I wouldn't enjoy chips and scratches. The exterior is fantastic and really does look as good as new.As for operating the phone, is it slow? Are the any issues using any of the apps? So far it works like a charm. No, I have not used all the apps. But of what I have used it works just fine. I stream fine, make calls and text fine, etc.The camera works great and everything is very clear on this phone. Even though the phone has a 5.5 inch screen, Apple did a great job of achieving slimness. I have a very protective case over the phone and it is still slim.If any of you are wondering about carriers I have Metro PCS and there are no issues. The phone connects great to my service provider. The phone only came with a charger, no manual or headphones. There are no issues with the charger.A negative review I read about the phone (a 64gb one and this applies to all other gb choices) is that you do not get as much memory as advertised. This is false. The software on the phone and apps will take up space. I believe about 14gb was used on the phone before I started using it. The phone is still a 128gb one.The seller of my item is BuySPRY.

Reviews: My neice was in real need of a new phone, and she had her heart set on an iPhone 6s. Since they're still really expensive we looked on amazon for a cheaper one. She plugged it in and it came right back on. After a few days has gone by it doesnt always do it anymore, so we're hoping maybe it was just a glitch. We're gonna buy a battery case so if it happens again she can just turn on the battery case. I did think about returning it, and even contacted the seller. They responded like twelve hours later apologizing and telling me if Id like a refund to initiate it thru amazon. My neice decided to just keep it. She really loves it and is happy with it.**EDIT**11/4 -changed my review from 3 to 4 stars.My neice told me that the battery seems to be working better now. Not sure if its the battery exactly, just that it isnt shutting off at 40% all the time anymore. Shes had it a couple months now and really loves it! So for the price, id definitely say this is worth trying out!

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: Well, I was very excited when I purchased this phone.  It looked good, too--a little scratch, but otherwise pretty decent.  Plus, 128 gig, finally I could save videos and aps and not have to worry about erasing something every couple of days.  So then I started using it to talk... major fail.  Even with the volume turned ALL THE WAY up, I could hardly hear the other person.  A lot of times I would call and I couldn't tell whether the phone was still ringing or the person had picked up.  To work around that I would put it on speaker, but then the other person could hardly hear me.  I started using earphones so that I could hear the phone and my callers could hear me (even when it was against my face).But then there were the battery issues... it would all of a sudden go from 7 % to dead, and then sometimes if I plugged it in it would jump up 20% immediately.  What?  What's that about?  Was it not reflecting the true charge or not holding the charge?  Once I was outside on a cooler day (maybe 50 degrees F) and the battery was at about 46%.  Suddenly it died.  Totally dead, from almost 50%... and I was expecting an important call.Then, similarly, a couple of days ago I had it at 60%.  I put it down, and when I picked it up again (about half an hour later) it was dead.  I mean DEAD.  No amount of plugging in could resuscitate it.  It was just gone.  Now I am a month and a half into using a "new" phone which is now dead.  I'm wondering whether it might be the battery, and whether it's worth replacing the battery which *might* be the (read: one) problem on an otherwise problematic phone, or to drop several hundred more dollars trying to replace it with another potentially faulty phone.  I enjoyed the extra storage, but in just about every other way I am not happy with this purchase.***Update: I spoke to Amazon about the purchase, and they came through for me once again!  Very pleased with Amazon customer service!  They make up for the shady sellers that sometimes come on here; even if you can't depend on all of the sellers, Amazon has your back!

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: Apple did a great job with this phone.  I bought this to replace my girlfriend's Galaxy S5, and she couldn't be happier!  The phone arrived quickly (Prime same-day), I cut my girlfriend's micro-SIM down to a nano-SIM (carefully) and popped it in, added her Google account with all of her email and contacts, and she was up and running, all within about 15 minutes!I use an iPhone SE for work, and a Galaxy S6 Edge the rest of the time.  The iPhone 6 is only slightly smaller and lighter than my S6, but it feels much thinner, much lighter, and is so much more comfortable to hold.  The S6 has a larger screen, and WAY more pixels, but the screen on the iPhone 6 looks way better to me.  Just like my iPhone SE, the iPhone 6 lasts all day on a single charge (unless you're playing Pokemon Go), and when the battery finally runs down, it charges back up in no time.Switching between WiFi and 4G (like when leaving my house in the morning) is so much smoother than with my S6.  With the S6, if I'm outside, with poor WiFi signal, I have to turn WiFi off to force the 4G connection, where the iPhone is completely seamless.I switched from iOS to Android after Apple stopped innovating (iPhone 4, 4S, 5, ...), switched from Samsung when they did the same (Galaxy S3, S4, S5), then from HTC when they also followed suit (HTC One M7, M8, M9).  I've been super happy with my S6 Edge for the past year, but I like the iPhone 6 so much, it might be time to make a move back to Apple for my primary, and order one of these for myself!The only complaint I have is the short, cheap lightning cable Apple ships with their phones.  I ordered some of the 6 ft. Amazon Basics cables (Apple Certified), and I'm expecting them to last at least twice as long as the Apple cable.Other thoughts: 16 GB?!  That leaves less than 10 GB usable after the space required for the OS.  Geez Apple, memory is so cheap!  Add more storage to your entry models or give me a micro-SD slot.
Reviews_bw: apple great job phone bought replace girlfriend galaxy happier phone arrived quickly prime day cut girlfriend micro sim nano sim carefully popped added google account email contacts running within minutes use iphone se work galaxy edge rest time iphone slightly smaller lighter feels much thinner much lighter much comfortable hold larger screen way pixels screen iphone looks way better like iphone se iphone lasts day single charge unless playing pokemon go battery finally runs charges back no time switching wifi g like leaving house morning much smoother outside poor wifi signal turn wifi force g connection iphone completely seamless switched ios android apple stopped innovating iphone switched samsung galaxy htc also followed suit htc one super happy edge past year like iphone much might time make move back apple primary order one complaint short cheap lightning cable apple ships phones ordered ft amazon basics cables apple certified expecting last least twice long apple cable thoughts gb leaves less gb usable space required os geez apple memory cheap add storage entry models give micro sd slot

But here I am, SIM card transferred and in my new phone that works just like it should. The EarPods work, I've yet to see if the charging equipment works because I already have some. Regardless, cosmetically, everything looks untouched and perfect. I'm so happy with my purchase, especially since I ordered it before the beginning of the year, before taxes were taken. 🤘🏼😅 Though it is nice to have money...it's even nicer to treat yourself with a phone you've wanted since its release. I ordered my iPhone 6 from Supreme Deals 18 and they DELIVERED. Thank you so much!!! I do recommend ordering from these people and may order again in the future.Edit: day two and my phone is having battery problems. I knew there had to be something wrong with it and it was too good to be true. So I'm sitting here playing Minecraft on my phone, it was at around 35%. It then warns I'm at 10%, so I click home and my phone is displaying 1%. Give. Me. A. Break. You've got a really bad battery and/or battery display. This is supposed to be brand new. Also I'm seeing on the edge of the phone near the corner of the display there are slivers of light shining through. That's not a huge problem, I'm just disappointed that my battery/battery display system or whatever isn't functioning. This phone should not only look brand new, but have brand new parts and be untouched by anyone. Will probably never buy electronics on Amazon again.

Having iCloud made restoring all of my settings a breeze, and, if my phone ever breaks, I won't lose any data since iCloud makes a backup every time the phone is plugged in and connected to wifi! I have not charged it since, besides listening to music through USB in my car when driving, and it's been almost a week.The build of this phone is beautiful. Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: Purchased phone from Digital Dealers which clearly indicated NEW.  When I received the item, the package was sealed and looked new but the plastic covering the phone (inside the box) clearly was reattached as it had air bubbles.  I did not think to much about it because the phone looked new.  A couple of days later the earbuds stopped working.  Since I thought the phone was new and under warranty, I took it to the Apple Store in the mall to get new earbuds.  The Apple folks looked up the serial number and to my surprise, told me the phone was put in service almost 2 years ago and was out of warranty and sent me on my way with no help.  Sending back for full refund.  Buyer beware.  If you buy, be sure to check warranty eligibility on Apple's site to make sure phone is new.
Reviews_bw: purchased phone digital dealers clearly indicated new received item package sealed looked new plastic covering phone inside box clearly reattached air bubbles not think much phone looked new couple days later earbuds stopped working since thought phone new warranty took apple store mall get new earbuds apple folks looked serial number surprise told phone put service almost years ago warranty sent way no help sending back full refund buyer beware buy sure check warranty eligibility apple site make sure phone new

Sometimes the phone shuts down when it has 35% battery or even full charge, and it only starts again if I put it to charge.. really frustrating.It happen just the first week after buying it, but I was abroad and couldn't leave a review..This time the iPhone was in "good" condition, fulfill by Amazon (recommended through the live chat with Amazon) . I expect second hand cell phones to have some scratches but I don't expect their software not to work after allegedly being tested by the seller..Honestly, very disappointing all this iPhone experience with Amazon.. :-(

Reviews: This was great! I bought this as a surprise gift for my mother's birthday. I was apprehensive because a few of my friends told me it wouldn't work where i live in the Caribbean (Turks & Caicos). It's almost been a month since ordering it and it's fully functioning and works with our Lime Carrier. The only negative i would've had was that the packaging was a bit dirty and the phone looked as though it was possibly used as the display phone in the apple store and then put into packaging. The battery was practically dead so i charged it before wrapping it. A plus though - atleast to me-  was that the home button was very sturdy so it'll be durable for long use.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: The whole time I’ve had the iPhone 6, I’ve been playing a game. I hand the phone to someone, and guess what phone they use based on their immediate reaction. iPhone users are always shocked by the sheer size of the 6; they all think it must be the 6 Plus. Android users, on the other hand, are unfazed. "This looks just like my phone," they all say.They’re not wrong. The iPhone 6 is 5.44 inches tall and 2.64 inches wide, which slots it right in between last year’s Moto X (also a 4.7-inch phone) and the new HTC One. It’s almost exactly the same size as Samsung’s Galaxy S5, just a little thinner and a little lighter. And it shares more in common with the world’s many Android phones — and the original, curvy iPhone — than with the sharp, rectangular iPhone 5S.THE IPHONE 6 IS THE BIG IPHONE FOR EVERYONEThe iPhone 5S was a stark piece of jewelry, a gorgeous object that was slightly cold and unapproachable. The iPhone 6 is far friendlier and far more usable. Mixing form and function this way is hard to do, and Apple gets it largely right.It’s simply and cleanly designed, with a metal back that curves cleanly around the sides. There are few seams and no ugly clutter. The only real flaw is the antenna design: Apple opted to essentially outline the top and bottom of the phone’s back with small plastic stripes where wireless radios can transmit signal. It just looks bad, like someone drew on my phone with a marker. HTC’s simple, striped design on the One M8 is far better, and even Apple’s glass-strip-on-the-top-and-bottom approach for the 5S looked nicer.In a weird way, slim and gorgeous as it is, this iPhone begs to have a case on it. (Apple makes some, including a really nice line of leather cases, and the third-party ecosystem is going to get even bigger.) It helps obscure the unsightly plastic strips, it makes the otherwise slick phone a little easier to grip, and it compensates for the awkwardly protruding camera lens on the back, which prevents the phone from sitting flat on a table. I’m worried I’m going to scratch the lens, and I’m annoyed that the phone wobbles. A case solves both problems.The 6 is big, much bigger than the 5S or the other iPhones that came before it. It’s even bigger than some other 4.7-inch phones; because Apple refuses to change the top and bottom bezels so as not to disturb the big home button, the phone is much taller than it needs to be. But it’s still usable in one hand and comfortable enough that I never feel terribly awkward using it. I have found myself holding it slightly differently, though: I tend to rest it on my fingers rather than grip it in my palm, the better to reach the farthest corners of the screen.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I got this one through TechnoMaster. Good seller this`s my 2nd iPhone Unlocked through this guys. This is iPhone 6 Model A1549, works with DIGITEL in Venezuela also LTE is properly working. I also try a Telefonica SIM in Mexico, and AT&T Sim in the US with no issues at all. Truly an unlocked one. Box come in original sealed package.Why I choose 3 stars? Well, I`ve been an iPhone user since 1st gen iPhone, iPhone3, iPhone4, iPhone 4S, iPhone 5, iPhone 5S and meanwhile this iPhone 6... I`ll always felt better with every new iPhone until this one. I believe iPhone 5S is equal or a little faster than this iPhone 6, also the user experience with phone proportions is better in iPhone 5S. Is really annoying need to use the "smart small screen" function (press home button in a tricky way) because the screen is so big that you need to use both hands for some functions. Yes the bigger screen is great when you have the time to browse the web, read your emails and so on, also to people with vision issues (the bigger letters are simple better), BUT for me, I use this iPhone mainly LIKE A PHONE, and it is just better the iPhone 5S size for FULL and faster functionality with only one hand.Also, I`m really MAD with iOs bugs, for example, if you use the "Vibrate/Sound" Button several times a day (I use it A LOT), well the iPhone just won`t sound at all, if you use Music it just muted, no matter how many times you press play/puse, stop, close all apps, turn switch to vibrate-sound  100times... if anoyone sent you a video through whatsapp it won`t sound, surfing the web: no sound, and so on... only fix: TURN OFF/ON your iphone... really??Another anyoning bug: Assistive touch function, I told you guys before that the screen is too big to use with only one hand, allright, iOs has this pretty cool function that shows a virtual HOME BUTTON into ur screen (I used it a lot in my last iPhone 5S), well you put this litte cool button in the middle left or right of the screen (to have it near of ur finger, right?) well, iOs just troll you and move it into the farest corner just to avoid you little finger to use it and have to use again: BOTH HANDS, ok you got me, where`s the hidden camera guys?...Another bug? iCloud control panel for windows sucks, iCloud photos stop sync (with PC or mac) when it wants, just simply dont work.Another one? Sometimes is just slow... with 5-10 apps openend or no one, iOs animation slows the use experience, even if you DISABLE animation in advance options...I`ve been using this iPhone6 for almost two months, and I`m not totally happy with it, its the more expensive phone I ever own, I wish I had for almost 1.000 bucks: the same coolest screen size, FASTER phone with a BRILLIANT iOS like it was in golden Apple years... this one its not the better I have owned.

Reviews: Unfortunately I was in a bind and desperately needed a new phone. I bought this phone because my old one was out of memory and was breaking down (had the phone for 2 years). Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: After seeing ~50% 5-star reviews and ~30% 1-star reviews, I decided to gamble on it. And I got unlucky.The seller, Vius, shipped the phone promptly, and at first glance, it looked good. Then I realized:- it had a number of dents and scratches, including one big one I could see from an arm's length. That alone violated what Amazon's "Certified Refurbished" guaranteed ("no visible cosmetic imperfections when held 12 inches away"). I don't know how Vius missed this.- the sockets (charging port, SIM card slot, earphone jack, even the speaker holes) had a lot of dirt in them. I found out when I couldn't properly fit the charging plug in. I've owned an iPhone 5 for almost four years, and I've never gotten my ports this clogged up...Well, I'm not too picky about that, actually. So I cleaned out all the ports and got down to checking the phone. My carrier could be detected (3G, calls, and SMS), memory indeed was 128Gb, camera and audio were working, and the display was great.Then I realized the battery was draining extremely quickly despite an initial 6-hour charge. After fully charging it twice more, I couldn't get it to last more than 6 hours. It would reach around 50% and then suddenly die. When opening the Settings > Battery portion, there was a notice that I needed to have the battery serviced.Granted, other sellers might give a better phone than what I got, so check the actual seller out before buying. I rated Vius with two stars because at least they delivered what I ordered on time and not some empty box. But in terms of the actual product, its good-as-dead battery makes it useless to me despite everything else working. What a shame.

Reviews: The good:  Phone looks excellent.The bad (well, annoying, but not bad bad) Battery was completely dead but seems to be taking a charge.  Won't be activating the phone (more on that) but I'm gonna let it charge and update this later.  (Update...phone activated on Straight Talk and seems to be working properly)The ugly:  I ordered "Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM (Certified Refurbished)" that clearly states in the description: Factory unlocked iPhones are GSM models and are ONLY compatible with GSM carriers like AT&T and T-Mobile as well as other GSM networks around the world. They WILL NOT WORK with CDMA carriers like Sprint, Verizon and the likes.  However...I just got the package and the phone has a "Carrier VERIZON Model IPhone 6 sticker on the back!  So....what exactly did I get?  Have to wait and see...I emailed the seller (DealFisher) and am trying to research the MEID and IMEI.  The model number for both is 1549 so that's not much help.Update:  Apple says it's unlocked and not identified as lost/stolen or anything bad like that.  DealFisher says it's unlocked too.  Jury is still out on issues with Straight Talk and Verizon and traveling, but phone seems to work and is in great shape, battery seems to be holding, and seller responded and is willing to work with me if there are issues...updated to 4 stars.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: The phone is great. I have it set up as a tracfone. Getting the Data working was a bit of pain. God bless them, but tracfone support are helpless when it comes to B.Y.O.phone. Turns out that to get the data to work you have to set up the A.P.N and M.M.C.S on an i-phone 6 but i.O.S will not let you manually adjust the settings. The link tracfone provides for setting up this profile Did Not Work, for me at any rate. After a lot of google research I discovered this app that sets it up for you, Unlockit.co.nz it worked like a dream. Now I have phone and data. I already had a tracfone log in so all I had left to do was down load the tracfone app from the app store so I could monitor my available minutes, s.m.s and data.I hope this helps others avoid a lot of frustration. Oh, and straight talk is basically tracfone so this might help those users as well.The phone itself looks brand new as far as I can tell. No scratches or ware and tare of any kind. No ear buds (as expected) but it did come with the wall charger and lighting to USB cable. Call clarity has improved (compared to i-phone 4) and Siri can be useful at times. I have also used the google maps navigation app and it is an adequate replacement for a stand alone GPS.I highly recommend getting some kind of cover/case. You don't really need a screen protector thanks to gorilla glass, but you will regret dropping this phone as the corners will show impacts. It is a slippery little devil, it almost jumps out of your hand like the "precious" thing it is.I think the size is just right and the "reach" feature is helpful. The only thing that would be better is battery life, and for the love of god let me expand the memory. This is the primary reason it only rates 4 stars.

Reviews: Right from the start this "certified refurbished"  phone was often unresponsive and frequently froze up. The only way to revive it was to do a hard power-off and reboot it, and even that only worked some of the times. I returned the phone and three weeks later got a replacement, which was even worse: I could not even activate it, as it was frozen from the start. Some on-line research has revealed that this problem is common with the iPhone 6: it is a design problem that has been labeled "Touch Disease". Apparently the touch chips on the logic board often partially break off and you get intermittent electrical connections. I'll have to take it to an Apple store and see what they can do about it.

Reviews: I bought this phone from Amazon's Certified Refurbished program. I was a little leery of buying a "secondhand" phone, but I have been an Amazon customer for many years, and have always had a great experience. The few times I've ever had a problem with anything I've purchased, (very few times in many years), Amazon has taken great care to correct any issues in a very expedient manner, so I have come to really trust them. I am a Prime Member, I use the Prime Pantry Feature, I buy things off the regular site, etc. So I was more than willing to give the "Certified Refurbished Phone Program" a chance. However, I still read EVERY single review from other people who had bought a phone this way. And although there were some less-than-completely-positive reviews, there were far more happy and satisfied customer, than not. So I bought my iPhone 6 (not S) and it arrived 4 days earlier than expected, it looks BRAND NEW, and it is in perfect working order!! I could not be more happy with my phone. I also had great faith that if  wasn't happy, Amazon would make it right. But fortunately, it is everything I was hoping it would be, and more! I was expecting to see some scratches on the glass, and the body, which I was already willing to live with, since the price was so good, plus free Prime shipping. But this phone arrived looking absolutely brand new, with a charger that has a nice long cable. I already had a case for it, and headphones, so I didn't need to buy any other accessories. I couldn't be happier or more impressed with this purchase!

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I purchased a certified refurbished 32GB iPhone 5S (Silver) for a family member. I was pleasantly surprised by the excellent condition of phone, it was cosmetically flawless. Also the phone was very professionally packaged for shipment, and included a USB charger and Lightning cable (these were 3rd-party non-Apple accessories, but they worked fine). We transferred the SIM card over from an older phone that was being retired, and the phone activated on the carrier network (AT&T in this case) with no problem. The only issue I ran into was that after a week or two of use, it became clear that the battery in the phone was worn/defective; the phone had trouble holding a charge for a full day, and would sometimes die when the battery percentage still showed 20-30%. So I ended up returning the unit for a full refund under the 30-day return policy, and ordering a second unit. The second phone was in similarly excellent condition, and the battery is working as expected.Overall I would say that going with a certified refurbished iPhone is a great value, you can get a phone that is just a couple years old, but is in excellent condition, and costs roughly 1/3 or less of the original price. I think a key is to take advantage of the Amazon 30-day return policy, which most of the third-party sellers here seem to honor (make sure you confirm this before you order). Inspect the phone carefully when you receive it, and make sure you test the battery thoroughly over a couple days to make sure it is in good condition. If either is not satisfactory, return it for a full refund within 30 days (which includes free return shipping), and simply order another unit.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I purchased this refurbished phone on Amazon and began using it in March of 2016. It's now October 2016 and it's virtually useless. Two things were immediately wrong with the phone. First, the back was significantly scratched up and did not appear new as promised. It was just cosmetic and I was going to use a case, so I didn't freak out. It is, after all, a refurbished phone. Also, since receiving the phone I have never been able to use it while it's plugged in. I didn't discover this until I already had it outside of the US, so I decided it wasn't worth the effort of getting it back to the US to exchange it. Now it makes me wonder if that was the first sign of the problems that I am now having. About a week ago the phone started randomly turning off and saying that it had a low battery in the middle of the day (it had previously lasted all day, easily). I would plug it in and when it turned back on it would say it was 40% charged still. This has gotten progressively worse each day until yesterday it began turning off after less than an hour while being 100% charged. I have tried restoring it along with various other suggestions on the internet, but it's not a software problem. When I removed the OtterBox that I'd been using I discovered that the screen is coming off, leading me to conclude that the battery is swelling (which would cause both the screen to detach and the phone to act as previously described). I have talked to the Authorized Apple repair technicians here in the country where I live, but they won't touch it if it's believed to be a swollen battery. They say that opening it will likely mean they couldn't close it again, it could cause someone harm, and that replacing the battery here costs 80% of the cost of a new phone anyway. Because it's refurbished and beyond the 90 days of guarantee, I have no recourse with Apple or the seller here. So, after only 7 months, I have a very expensive paperweight. Proceed with caution.

I never even thought that was the problem, as the phone looked really good and clean. I just cleaned it out and it's perfect again.The phone works great. Battery is great (it's better than my year old 5s). The phone doesn't have visible damages and the screen looks great.The only real problem is that the lightning port is a bit loose, and you need to position the lightning cable a certain way (push it to the right) to get the connection to work. At least, that's the case with 2 of my original Apple lightning cables, and 2 of my Amazon cables (and these cables work fine with my older iPhone). The cable that came with the phone seems to fit this phone better and you don't need to keep it positioned a certain way, why it's like that I don't know. I would return it but I really need the phone right now, and I can live with it anyway. So it's just something to look into with these refurbished models.

My two star rating is for the battery.  Perhaps this is iOS 10, however I've researched the Tips App and followed suggestions for reducing battery life but it remains nil.  My previous iPhone 5S would hold a charge for 2 days of moderate use.  I am lucky to get 1 day with this iPhone 5S!  Also, the battery dies once the percentage indicator goes below 7%.For purchasing a refurbished phone, I would expect the seller to install a new battery.  They sell for about $17 on Amazon, so why not!Update: After one week of daily use, I Thoroughly irritated with the poor performance of the battery.  I've had to recharge three times in one day.  I've resorted to keeping a backup power supply with me at all times.Although this is a great phone, what good is it  if the battery is dead?

Reviews: After loosing my phone again I needed a relatively cheap option and I didn't really care if it is used or not or how old or new it would be. I only cared if it worked and was cheap enough so that I would not regret loosing it or breaking again. I firmly believe that once you go to apple you never go back, so there was no question about the brand of the phone I was going to get. I really like how user friendly apple is and how well acquainted I am to it, just makes things easier. So I started looking for a cheap option on amazon. Another thing I really cared about was that the iPhone should have been unlocked, coz I was not planning on buying a sim card of any kind, but rather using my phone with wifi. Having these things in mind I knew that I most probably will not find the best possible option, it is almost impossible to find completely unlocked phones. Whatsoever, I ordered this one after having asked if it is unlocked to not and receiving a positive response. In short, the phone was not unlocked, but thankfully it only took few minutes to unlock it with my friend's sim card. There were no scratches on the phone (almost none). Works pretty well and I have been using it for over half year. So far no complaints, will update if I find any.Overall I am greatly satisfied with the phone though it doesn't perfectly fit the description.Update: I took the phone to the at&t for the purpose of buying a sim card. The girl who was trying to insert the card, couldn't close it afterwards and she broke that spot(meaning it is not broken, but doesn't fully close/go in). She took no responsibility whatsoever at all on her part, which was pretty annoying, but later on I took it to the apple store. they told me that this happened most probably (but not certainly) because it was a refurbished phone and that it will cost me about 40$ to get it fixed. But since I changed my mind about buying a sim card I did not go for fixing it.

Reviews: After loosing my phone again I needed a relatively cheap option and I didn't really care if it is used or not or how old or new it would be. I really like how user friendly apple is and how well acquainted I am to it, just makes things easier. So I started looking for a cheap option on amazon. Another thing I really cared about was that the iPhone should have been unlocked, coz I was not planning on buying a sim card of any kind, but rather using my phone with wifi. Having these things in mind I knew that I most probably will not find the best possible option, it is almost impossible to find completely unlocked phones. Whatsoever, I ordered this one after having asked if it is unlocked to not and receiving a positive response. In short, the phone was not unlocked, but thankfully it only took few minutes to unlock it with my friend's sim card. There were no scratches on the phone (almost none). So far no complaints, will update if I find any.Overall I am greatly satisfied with the phone though it doesn't perfectly fit the description.Update: I took the phone to the at&t for the purpose of buying a sim card. The girl who was trying to insert the card, couldn't close it afterwards and she broke that spot(meaning it is not broken, but doesn't fully close/go in). She took no responsibility whatsoever at all on her part, which was pretty annoying, but later on I took it to the apple store. they told me that this happened most probably (but not certainly) because it was a refurbished phone and that it will cost me about 40$ to get it fixed. But since I changed my mind about buying a sim card I did not go for fixing it.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: So far, so good. My wife's 5 year old Iphone 5 accidentally dropped into water, and stopped working immediately. She has become extremely dependent on her phone, so losing it caused great pain and suffering and required a replacement right away.As everyone knows, the carriers no longer offer free or discounted replacement phones every two years like they used to. We have AT&T Wireless service and didn’t want to be locked into another two year contract with an expensive payment plan, so we took a chance with a refurbished Iphone 5S from Amazon. It arrived sooner than promised. It came in a generic white box, with a charger plug and cable, but did not include headphones, a manual, or a SIM card. The phone appeared to be in like-new condition – no dents, scratches, etc.I went on Google and searched for a way to remove the sim card from her old phone and inset it into the new phone, and found a video on YouTube. It was pretty easy. The new phone was discharged and needed to be charged, so I did this.Once it charged for a while and had some life, I connected the phone to our WIFI network, turned it on, and followed the instructions. It loaded the new IOS 10 software. Keep in mind there’s no manual, so that’s about all the instructions provided cover.It’s a little confusing how to set the Iphone up. It was difficult navigating the AT&T & Apple site, so I wasn’t sure what data was already on the sim card, and was concerned I would wipe everything out if I chose the wrong option (i.e. restore Iphone, or set up new Iphone). “Restore Iphone” gave a scary warning, so I chose “set up new Iphone” and it seemed to work.Prior to being dunked in water, my wife had irregularly backed up the contacts and apps from her old phone onto our home computer via Itunes and the Icloud, but apparently her photos & notes didn’t get backed up, so unfortunately that data was lost. Luckily I had manually backed up her photos on our computer a few months ago, so luckily not everything was lost.She's only had the phone a few days, but the battery life seems good. Overall, the refurbished Iphone 5S that we purchased from Amazon seems like a good choice.

Product_name: Apple iPhone 6 16GB Factory Unlocked GSM 4G LTE Internal Smartphone - Space Gray
Reviews: I purchased this phone and noticed something odd about it: the camera sound could not be silenced in any way. I did some research and found out that the reason for this is that the phone originated in Japan where there is a law requiring phones to have an audible camera sound. The information about the phone never stated that the phone could be from another country, and thus have different settings than the American counterparts. Another issue was that the phone screen had a crack in it the day after I had received this phone. I had not really used it yet because I need to get it set up still, and yet there the crack was. I contacted the seller, stating the problem and that the phone shouldn't have a problem after not being used. I was told by the seller that though there is a 90-day warranty on the phone, the warranty does not cover physical damage. Overall, I feel that this product was incredibly misrepresented to me, and it will not be somewhere I will look for a phone in the future.

I went with this instead of Gazelle because this has a 90 day warranty on it I think Gazelle only has 30. Plus Gazelle makes you pay more for "fair, good or excellent" quality. I think this one you just pay one price and get a decent phone. Could be a crap shoot though but I would say mine is somewhere between good and excellent condition. I would use this again instead of buying a new phone for 3x the price.
